The '''Parc La Grange''', [[Geneva]], has a surface of 200,000&nbsp;m<sup>2</sup>, hosts very old and tall trees, Geneva's biggest rose garden, orangeries and an 18th-century villa. Also two theaters, a playground as well as a paddling pool for the children are found there. It is situated at the [[Quai Gustave-Ador]] in Geneva.
{{coord|46.206|6.167|dim:1000_region:CH|display=title}}
