[[Serbia]]n [[postal code]]s consist of five digits. The first two digits roughly correspond to the corresponding [[Districts of Serbia|district]]; district seat cities usually have 000 as the last three digits, while smaller towns and villages have non-round last three digits.
According to http://www.posta.rs/AdresniKod/Adresovanje_eng.asp, since 1 January 2005 a six-digit postcode format has been introduced. {{compact ToC|side=yes|top=yes|num=yes}}
