{{Unreferenced stub|auto=yes|date=December 2009}}
'''Vakaippathi''', one among the [[Panchappathis]] is a holy site for the People of [[Ayyavazhi]]. 

Vakaippathi is the place situated 4&nbsp;km northeast to [[Kanyakumari (town)|Kanyakumari]] in the seashore near [[vattakkotai]]. This is the place where 700 families from [[Swamithoppe]] were sent to [[Thuvayal Thavasu]] by [[Ayya Vaikundar]]; they were later known as [[Thuvayal Pantarams]]. This pathi is not included in Pancha pathis.

